               <head>Commentary by Jahaniyan on Sharafnamah of Nizami</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Sharaf 'nāmah by Muḥammad Jahāniyān ibn Muḥammad Shāh ibn Fatḥ al-Dīn Chishtī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006007951 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1246-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Lengthy and detailed commentary by Muḥammad Jahāniyān ibn Muḥammad Shāh ibn Fatḥ al-Dīn Chishtī on the 
                <title key="work_22954">Sharaf 'nāmah</title>, part of the 
                <title key="work_22954">Iskandar'nāmah</title>mas̲navī (comprised of the 
                <title key="work_22954">Sharaf'nāmah</title>and 
                <title key="work_22954">Khirad'nāmah</title>) from the Khamsah by Ḥakīm Abū Muḥammad Ilyās Ganjavī "
                <persName key="viaf_2474895" role="ant">Niẓāmī</persName>" (d. 614/1217).
                        </p>
                        <p>This copy is characterised by orthographical and scribal errors.</p>
                        <p>Diagrams, tables, and annotations in margins.</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 142r): completed by Muḥammad Muḥkam Dīn ibn Hidāyat Allāh resident of Muḥammadpūr, written for himself, Vaysākh samvat 1875.</p>
                        <p>Rough nastaʿlīq.</p>
                        <p>Pencil foliation.</p>
                        <p>Old paper dust wrapper (fourth schedule of BEIC legal publication for 1851 drafted by Fred. Jas. Halliday, Secy. to the Gov. of India); watermark (lion rampant guardant in crowned oval, not dated); annotations in Bangālī.</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound.</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22954">Ḥall-i mushkilāt va kashf-i lughāt-i Sharaf'nāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22954">حلّ مشكلات و كشف لغات شرف نامه</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8027">Muḥammad Jahāniyān ibn Muḥammad Shāh ibn Fatḥ al-Dīn Chishtī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8027">محمّد جهانيان ابن محمّد شاه ابن فتح الدّين چشتى</persName>
                     </author>
